Go to GoDaddy domain and copy it and paste it in Route53
Enter subdomain as something --> abc.yourgodaddydomain
Create public hosted zone

Then copy 4 ns created in Route53 to godaddy->domain->manage->ns -> one by one enter all 4 with name/host as route 53 domain (abc here)

Create an S3 Bucket
create a server name--kops for example
There install awscli, kops and kubectl
Configure aws user with admin privilege (otherewise choose policies and create some of them for kubernetes cluster purpose)
